OL,3,C'We loved her': 100 years since
OL,4,CGuernsey's first female deputy was
OL,5,Celected
OL,7,Ffirst female Deputy, Marie Louise
OL,8,FMansell Randall, is being honoured
OL,9,Fwith a blue plaque at her first home
OL,10,Fin St Peter Port today (Wednesday 24
OL,11,FJanuary) to mark 100 years since her
OL,12,Felection.JDeputy Randall was 42 when
OL,13,Fshe was appointed in January 1924 and
OL,14,Fserved for 31 years, making her the
OL,15,Fonly female member of the States for
OL,16,F24 of those 31 years.
OL,18,FThis came 24 years before Jersey's
OL,19,Ffirst female , who was elected in 1945.
