OL,3,C'We loved her': 100 years since
OL,4,CGuernsey's first female deputy was
OL,5,Celected
OL,7,FShelaine Green, Chair of Women in
OL,8,FPublic Life said: "Marie Randall was a
OL,9,Fpioneer, elected just four years after
OL,10,FNancy Astor first sat in the UK
OL,11,FParliament and 24 years before
OL,12,FJersey's Ivy Forster.J"It's hard to
OL,13,Fbelieve that, 100 years after Marie
OL,14,Fwas first elected, there are still
OL,15,FonlyJeight women among the 40 members
OL,16,Fof the States.
OL,18,F"We hope Marie's story will inspire
OL,19,Fother Guernsey women to follow in her
OL,20,Ffootsteps ` and we'd of course be very
OL,21,Fhappy to support them."
