OL,4,CGuernsey's first female deputy was
OL,5,Celected
OL,7,FDeputy Randall, who was educated in
OL,8,FThe Ladies' College, volunteered as a
OL,9,Fmember of the Voluntary Aid Detachment
OL,10,Fin World War 1 and nursed in Guernsey,
OL,11,FRouen and London.
OL,13,FShe was made an MBE in 1954 retired
OL,14,Ffrom the States in 1955 and died in
OL,15,F1965.
